@NODE 1. "Introduction"

@{B}    Introduction:
@{UB}
The shareware program GOLDED from Dietmar Eilert is one of the best Editors
at the shareware market.  But this editor can only play existing ARexx-Macros
and otherwise save command sequences in a binary file.  It is not possible
to edit this command sequences.  Therefore it is not possible to record a
macro with the editor as a minimum file and to edit this file later to suit
the full needs.

But this is possible with my program.  You have to record a command sequence,
which has to be saved.  By starting the program this sequence will be converted
to an Arexx-Macro, which can be edited with a normal editor.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "Installation"

@{B}    Installation of the program:
@{UB}
As this is a simple CLI-program, no installation is necessary for the
program.  It is useful to copy the program into the Arexx-Drawer of
the editor GoldEd.  Of course to use the program it is necessary to have
the editor GoldEd by Dietmar Eilert.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 3. "Usage"

@{B}    Usage of the program:
@{UB}
The program is a CLI-program.  A usage from the workbench is not
implemented.

The program will be started in the following way:

GED_seq2ARexx <Inputfile> [<Outputfile> [<Sceletonfile>]]

If you call the program without any parameter, a short describtion
of the program will be shown.

Describtion of the parameters:

Inputfile: this must be a command sequence of the program GOLDED.
If necessary a file extension of <.seq> will be appended by the program.

Outputfile: this is the name of the ARexx-macro file, which will be
produced by the program.  The file may not exist.  If the file has
been written without a file extension, an extension of <.ged> will be
appended.  If no outputfile is written, the name of the inputfile with
a file extension of <.ged> is used.

Sceletonfile: This is the name of the sceletonfile.  As some startup
(e.g. "Locking" of the editor) and shutdown (e.g. "Unlocking" of the
editor) is necessary, this informations will be provided in the
sceletonfile.  A standard sceletonfile with name "GED_seq2ARexx.ged"
is already provided.  If no other sceletonfile will be written in the
command line, this file will be used as default.  Of course this file
can be changed according to requirement.

Describtion of the sceletonfile:
At the begin there is the startup code.
This ends with the character @, which must be the only char in a line.
All following of the file will be the shutdown code.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Remarks"

@{B}    Remarks:
@{UB}
All key inputs and menu actions should be converted correct by the program.
Mouse actions in the document, as changing the place of the cursor or
hiliting of text with the mouse will not be converted correct.
For a correct conversion these have to be done by key inputs or menu
actions.  Furthermore in the moment there will be converted no additional
key inputs at requestors.  These have to be inputed manually at the
ARexx-macro.

@ENDNODE

